                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1426: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Feely</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-15T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 15, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>59. Your 126, October 15, 10 a.m. The matter contained in the first paragraph of
                    your telegram has been under consideration for some time, and the Department
                    hopes to send you a further telegram about it either at the end of this week or
                    the beginning of next.</p>
                <p>With regard to the second paragraph the Department feels it most advisable that
                    Bolivia accept November 11 as the date for the opening of the meeting even
                    though Dr. Finot may not be able to reach Washington by that date. Although the
                    Department, of course, cannot speak for the others, it feels certain that there
                    will be no objection at the meeting of November 11 to a postponement until Dr.
                    Finot arrives.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
